SIMPLE: nab
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nab
<hw>Nab</hw> <pr>(n⟦acr⟧b)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. <er>Knap</er>,
<er>Knop</er>, <er>Knob</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The summit of an
eminence.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Firearms)</fld> <def>The cock of a gunlock.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Locksmithing)</fld> <def>The keeper, or box into
which the lock is shot.</def> <rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nab</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nab
<hw>Nab</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Nabbed</conjf> <pr>(n⟦acr⟧bd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Nabbing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Dan <ets>nappe</ets>, or Sw.
<ets>nappa</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To catch or seize suddenly or
unexpectedly.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Smollett.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To capture; to arrest; <as>as, the police nabbed the
culprit trying to hide in the basement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nabit</ent>⟦br⟧
